Oct 18 2009 	Nice Stay But Beware of Priority Club Promotional Bonuses	My wife and I booked a trip within the specified promotion period on the Intercontinental Hotel's website back in June. We had an enjoyable stay in downtown San Francisco on Howard St, June 22 - 27, 2009 to celebrate our wedding anniversary. The staff was very helpful in sharing their knowledge of the city's attractions and restaurant recommendations. Our suite was clean with a great view of the city and the buffet breakfast was pleasantly better than expected.Unfortunately we don't have the same to say about the online booking. The ICH site was running an online promotion at the time: 1 free night for each 2 nights qualifying stay booked within the promotional period (our booking dates and stay was within the specified period). We immediately booked our 5 night stay as there was no indication our booking did not otherwise qualify. We paid $199 per night + taxes for a King Suite that included a complimentary breakfast. We thought it was a good deal considering we would get 1 free night for each 2 nights stay. This was our deciding factor for not booking elsewhere for at least $50 less per night at a comparable hotel like the Hilton. Upon our return we logged into our Priority Club rewards account and it noted our stay during the free night stay promotional period had &quot;expired&quot;. To our surprise, we were informed the rack rate for our stay was already heavily discounted and did not qualify for the free nights bonus. We were also referred to the small print in one paragraphs of the terms and conditions. What really irked us was finding out the original invoice and record of our stay had been modified/deleted from our online account. The online record now only shows the dates we stayed and comment &quot;Non-qualifying nights stay&quot;. Our invoice with extra charges we paid room service is nowhere to be found.We feel we were mislead by a deceptive marketing tactic that did not make clear that our stay did not qualify upfront. We are very disappointed the ICH and expected far better customer service having enjoyed a previous stay with this chain in Moorea/Tahiti. So beware to other travellers and not assume your online booking via the ICH website qualifies for any promotional bonuses unless you get it confirmed in writing.	
