Sep 7 2009 	Very nice hotel	We stayed for 6 days a couple of weeks ago in a lovely deluxe room on the 29th floor with views out to the sea. Nicely decorated, plenty of space for two adults and a teenager. The pool is still not fixed though which was disappointing.We did not eat at the hotel but after arriving in the evening we went to the Italian just opposite. It does not look terribly appealing but a relative who lives locally recommended it as a cheap and cheerful and it was perfect if you are tired and just want to have some (pretty decent) pasta and drinks without too much effort or cost. We also went to the local Westfield food hall just on the other side of Bloomingdales for lunch and supper a couple of times when we did not want to go somewhere too posh or expensive - great value but rather canteen like atmosphere. The great find there is Out the Door - part of The Slanted Door group but somewhat cheaper. We loved Mel's Diner for Breakfast - they were doing steak and eggs for $8.95.I too can't understand why people say it is a long walk to places. Very easy to get to Union Square and the cable cars. Staff were friendly but I did not find the Concierge particularly helpful. The guys at the door and valet parking were great. Don't forget there is a courtesy car available in the mornings and late afternoon. We took it one morning and it made a pleasant change to travel in a chauffeur driven merc!I would go back to this hotel without any hesitation.	
