Jul 29 2009 	Not a good location for tourism	We stayed for a weekend at this hotel. The hotel is fine, with nice rooms. But unless you are attending a convention (in which case it is very well situated), the location is not good for tourists. AT ALL. The hotel is a VERY LONG walk from North Beach and Chinatown, two of our favorite areas. It's even a pretty long walk to Union Square. The immediate surroundings of the hotel are very boring. The hotel is on Howard which is a wide (four lane) one-way street, with cars zipping by at a good clip. In short, the surroundings feel like the warehouse district that SOMA used to be and, in many ways, still is. Maybe in 20 years, the neighborhood will have developed some character. For now, stay closer to Union Square, where the vibrancy of San Francisco is more easily seen.	
