Jul 27 2009 	Excellent service - good deals with packages on site	Stayed at the Intercontinental for one night at the beginning of an anniversary road trip that started in SF. I had booked a package through their site that included a Corner Junior Suite, parking, buffet (including gratuity), and two trolley tickets. Upon arriving we were warmly greeted and were told we had been upgraded to a King Bedroom Suite which featured a living room, bedroom, two flat screens and 1.5 baths (the half bath had a view of the city) on the 31st floor. There was a room length window seat in the living area that my GF loved. The view was awesome. The hald bayh also had a window opposite the sink. The room was immaculate - minus a bird poop smear on the exterior top of the living room window. We left the room for a bit and returned to find that complimentary champagne had been delivered while we were out. Sweet!We never used the trolley tickets. However, I did want to point out that we receive pre-printed tickets at check-in. Someone else here posted that they were only reimbursed for the cost of these. This was not the case with us.After dinner we hung out with friends until well past 2AM. When we returned to the hotel, the valet section appeared to be full. There was a slight communication problem with the attendant (he was nice but did not speak English very well) as we were trying to explain that we had prepaid parking. He was trying to send us over to another deck that was cheaper to save us money. He finally saw my valet tag on my keychain, apologized for the misunderstanding (I think), and took our car. A bit of a snafu, but it wasn't too big a deal.The breakfast buffet was relatively high end food and delicious. Yogurt in a martini glass, anyone?We left the next morning. Our room came in less than the estimated price on their site (by $10). Valet was a bit slow - but friendly. We drive out of the city for a couple of hours and I realize that I left my camera in the room (I had been taking pictures of the room before we left). I immediately called and was connected to Gloria in housekeeping. She assured me that they found the camera and could ship it to our next destination. I wound up having to call two days later (due to spotty cell service in yosemite) and she remembered me, playfully scolded me for not calling the day before, and promised to send the camera to my home. It arrived by Fedex the day after we returned. Thank you Gloria, you rock!I don't usually write reviews, but I feel as if the service I received at the Intercontinental warranted a very positive one. I will stay here again. Check the packages they offer on their site (especially those that include the $50 parking fee) as I found it to be a much better deal than booking a room here elsewhere.Safe travels...	
