Jun 6 2009 	Fabulous hotel great staff but a few annoyances	Stayed here for 7 nights while attending a conference at another hotel. I liked the location and the design, and the staff are certainly well-trained and service-oriented. Like most SF hotels of this level, nothing comes cheap -- internet charges are the most outrageous, at $16/day (though there are discounts for 3 and 5 day use). A tap beer at the 888 bar was $8.50. My king room on the 18th floor looked west towards downtown and was very quiet. Bathroom was very nice and had a walk-in, tiled shower. Most nights (but not all) I got turndown service. A major annoyance was the unadjustable desk chair. It sat way too low and couldn't be raised, an ergonomic problem if you needed to work at the desk. And I needed to, since the wireless internet signal was so weak as to be useless -- meaning I were limited to wired service only. A daily local newspaper was provided rather than the usual USA Today. I found the location ideal for me (two city blocks to Market St) and the surrounding neighborhood was completely comfortable and safe. Many good restaurants are within an easy walk. I did not eat in the well-reviewed hotel restaurant (Luce) or use room service, but the food I ate at the bar was excellent. Every staff member I encountered was top-notch, friendly and helpful. There is a decent fitness facility and very nice lap pool and whirlpool, but no changing area. The adjacent spa does have (small) locker rooms with steam rooms, but that is an extra $20 access fee per day. In short, a really nice hotel but lots of expensive extras.	
