Jan 15 2009 	Excellent rooms good view a few minutes away from Union Square	We spent 6 days at the Intercontinental in San Francisco and the hotel consistently delivered on all counts. The hotel is fairly new, and this shows in the modern design and spacious rooms. Our room was on a high floor, and we had a good view across the city and further on to the bay. The bed was very comfortable, and the room also had a large 42&quot; lcd. the bathroom has a large walk-in shower, but no bathtub. The whole length of one wall in the room is lined by windows, making the room very bright and airy.The service is excellent at all levels - efficient and quick valet parking, a knowledgeable and helpful concierge, friendly housekeeping. We ordered room service on a few occasions and felt that the food, although not stellar, was certainly at a very good level.The only slight negative was that the air conditioning didn't seem to work evenly in the room and bathroom, and the bathroom remained rather cold. I also would have liked better shower pressure - this wasn't bad, but it wasn't a proper power shower either.The hotel is well-located, right next to the Moscone convention center and only a couple of blocks away from Union Square. I enjoy walking, so the few minutes that it took to get to the more happening parts of town did not bother me.Finally, the hotel itself has an excellent restaurant, Luce, that is certainly worth trying. I would definitely recommend this hotel, both for business and leisure travelers - an excellent example of Intercontinental quality.	
